title: Shares of several hotels, restaurants & leisure companies are trading higher following strong US jobs data and continued optimism amid the reopening of the economy.

Shares of several companies in the broader consumer discretionary space are trading higher as markets continue to gain on optimism over an economic reopening as well as a smaller-than-expected drop in nonfarm payrolls. The economy reopening could mean more consumer spending which is good for the sector.

Shares of several restaurant companies are trading higher amid optimistic coronavirus outlook following positive drug data from Gilead. This has raised hopes of a sooner return to spending and economic activity.
Shares of several restaurant, fast food and dining companies are trading lower amid continued uncertainty around demand caused by the coronavirus which has significantly decreased consumer spending.

Shares of several restaurant, fast food and dining companies are trading higher amid positive market sentiment on speculation some coronavirus hotspots could soon level off. A sooner recovery could mean a sooner reopening of restaurants.

Shares of several restaurant companies are trading higher amid positive market sentiment on optimism of cases potentially leveling off in some hotspots globally. Lower cases could mean a sooner return to store openings and spending by consumers.

Shares of several restaurant companies are trading higher amid overall market strength. Restaurants have been negatively impacted amid lockdown measures to curb the spread of the coronavirus, though delivery and drive-thru names have remained open.
